<strong>IN&#45;TEXT CITATION</strong>
<br>
<br>
Use the organisation name (organisations include private companies, government agencies, and 
institutions) and year each time you refer to the work. 
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	The Turning Page Bookshop (2020) explains that&hellip;
	<br>
	Alternatively: &hellip;outlined in their business profile (The Turning Page Bookshop, 2020).
</blockquote>
<br>
The organisation&#8217;s name may be abbreviated if the work will be cited at least three times 
in your assignment. In the first citation write the organisation name in full, including the 
abbreviation. For subsequent citations, use the abbreviation.
<br>
<strong>First in&#45;text citation</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	The Department of Education, Employment and Workplace Relations (DEEWR, 2020) described&hellip;
	<br>
	Alternatively: &hellip;as a recent study has shown (Department of Education, Employment 
	and Workplace Relations [DEEWR], 2020).
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Subsequent in&#45;text citations</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	DEEWR (2020) described&hellip;
	<br>
	&hellip;as recent evidence suggests (DEEWR, 2020).
</blockquote>
<br>
If you are using a direct quotation, consisting of fewer than 40 words, enclose the quote using 
double quotation marks. As webpages do not usually contain page numbers, include either a heading 
or section name, a paragraph number, or a combination of a section name with a paragraph number 
in lieu of page numbers.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	The Department of Education, Employment and Workplace Relations (DEEWR, 2020) reports that 
	&#34;government funding has been reduced by 15%&#34; (Funding section, para.4).
	<br>
	Alternatively: As a result, &#34;government funding has been reduced by 15%&#34; 
	(Department of Education, Employment and Workplace Relations [DEEWR], 2020, Funding 
	section, para. 4).
</blockquote>
<br>
If the quotation is greater than 40 words, the quote is displayed in a double spaced, 
indented block at 1.27cm from the left margin. Do not use double quotation marks to enclose 
a block quotation.
<br>
<br>
If you wish to cite an <strong>entire website</strong>, without mentioning particular information 
from a specific webpage, it is not necessary to include the website in your reference list. 
Instead, provide the URL in parentheses.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Workcover is a useful work health and safety website for information and documents about 
	addiction (<span class="fake-aref">http://www.workcover.nsw.gov.au/newlegislation2012/Pages/default.aspx</span>).
</blockquote>
